This was an excellent meal n I’m a real pain in the neck to satisfy. Lots of specific detailed requests too. I’ve seen this place n used to live around the corner from it but never tried it lol. Why? Because I thought it didn’t look “authentic” enough or “legit” enough. That’s pretty lame of me n I should know better. Similar thing happened recently n I judged a book by its cover. I mean it’s not a chipotle or Taco Bell or anything like that, it just isn’t a little “dive” n that’s usually my fav.  I had Mojarra Frita which is a whole fried fish (porgy) n it’s not always great at all places. Even though it’s a relatively simple dish, it can easily be awful for sooo many reasons. Well not with these guys. RIDICULOUSLY AMAZING n possibly the best one I’ve had within 4 miles. Crazy to me bc it’s been on my radar for literally years n I coulda been enjoying it this whole time. The fish was so fresh n delicious n perfectly cooked. I mean down to a window of 30 seconds — perfection!!!! So sec either way n it wouldn’t have been “perfect”. Check out the pic — fantastic.

Castro’s lost me as a customer at the beginning of 2019. I guess by my being a regular Castro’s took me for granted. Thought I would settle for anything. I ordered hot lunch and dinner delivery priced at $20.15. Tipped the delivery person $5.00. Not a freezing day, the temperature topped out at 48 degrees. I live 0.2 miles away. While I did expect the order to take some time to arrive, as Castro’s has become pretty popular, I did not expect it to arrive cold. Not chilled. Cold. Ok, so to err is human. Politely, I telephoned. Castro’s offered no solution. I decided to go and retrieve my money. And, make no mistake, Castro’s made sure to direct me to bring the food with me. My last visit, my last order.

Went here with my girlfriend the day after valentine's day. The food was delicious. I got Castro style pancakes, western omelette which comes with hash browns/toast and sausage. She got waffles, western omelette and goat tacos (which we split). Everything was delicious!!! We also got chips and salsa. Walnuts sprinkled on top made a world of difference for me. I'm familiar with the option at places all over but always opted out. Slices of strawberries, banana with whipped cream and syrup on top of my pancakes was absolute bliss. No complaints on anything. Had their interpretation of a strawberry banana milkshake, it was refreshing and fruity. The tacos were savory and delicious with a soft shell. I'm looking forward to going back for breakfast/brunch again.

I was wandering around my neighborhood and decided to stop here for breakfast. This place has a lot of seating and even a nice patio out back. The restrooms are large, clean and well stocked! I think I should've asked them to not go easy on the jalapenos though. Sopa Azteca: The broth was rich, the avocado was perfectly ripe, and the oaxaca cheese matched it all perfectly.
